node.text:
Details on coronavirus infection in Amman Health Centre.

Amman Health Centre has returned to work after it was closed yesterday, Sunday, following the recording of a coronavirus infection of one of its employees.

The centre took all precautionary measures to limit the spread of coronavirus, according to Head of the centre Raed al-Shboul.

Three sections will remain closed until Saturday. The sections are radiology, maternity and genetic diseases.

The infected nurse, who was working in the genetic diseases department, she is not one of the permanent staff members centre, but was brought in from another centre when more staff were needed, said al-Shboul.

Home quarantine was imposed on 15 of the centre's staff who came into close contact with the infected nurse, and samples were taken from all the staff working in the centre, added al-Shboul.

The Amman Health Centre is one of the largest health centres in Jordan. as It contains approximately 80 clinics, and there are more than 75 specialist doctors, and the centre reviews about 1,500 medical cases daily across all departments.

#Amman #coronavirus #covid19 #Jordan
